metadata.name: German Shepherd
metadata.description:
In 2163, the german shepherd is nearly extinct due to its sensitivity to the 1000G radioactivity. A French scientist is able to clone the original breed back to a somewhat normal state. Unfortunately, the lack of brain stems in the clones made them a little slower than the original breed.

1/1 edition - video | 3000 x 3000 pixels

Over the course of over 140 years, animals changed and mutated. They developed syndromes and abnormalities that couldnâ€™t be explained in any other way than a result of human interference.

This series of artworks are based on predictions from our times Nostradamus, Kalle Ranes.
